description.description: A human-readable description for a thing.

encoding.description: The encoding of the data. This is not the same as the media type. Rather, this is the encoding of the data in a more specific sense, e.g., UTF-8, ASCII, etc.

format.description: The format of the data. This is not the same as the media type. Rather, this is the format of the data in a more specific sense, e.g., CSV, JSON, etc.

hash.description: The hash representation of the data, e.g., sha256, md5, etc. Subtypes have their own slots.

id.description: A unique identifier for a thing.

keywords.description: Keywords associated with the data. These may be provided by the data creator or assigned later in a manual or automated manner.

last_updated_on.description: Date and Time at which the element was last updated

md5.description: The md5 hash representation of the data.

media_type.description: The media type of the data. This is not the same as the format. Rather, this is the media type of the data in a more general sense, e.g., text/csv, application/json, etc., though as it is defined here the media type can be any string.

sha256.description: The sha256 hash representation of the data.

status.description: Status of the element in terms of its maturity or life cycle

title.description: the official title of the element

description: A collection of related datasets, likely containing multiple files of multiple potential purposes and properties.

compression.description: The compression format of the data. This is not the same as the media type. Rather, this is the compression format of the data in a more specific sense, e.g., zip, gzip, etc.

conforms_to.description: The standard to which the data conforms. This is not the same as the media type. Rather, this is the standard to which the data conforms in a more specific sense, e.g., frictionless, schema.org, etc. This should be a standard from the Bridge2AI standards registry.

conforms_to_class.description: The class in the schema to which the data object instantiates.

conforms_to_schema.description: The schema to which the data conforms. This is not the same as the media type. Rather, this is the schema to which the data conforms in a more specific sense, and even more specific than the general set of standards it conforms to.

created_on.description: Date and Time at which the element was created

description.description: A human-readable description for a thing.

doi.description: The Digital Object Identifier of the data, with the doi prefix.

download_url.description: URL from which the data can be downloaded. This is not the same as the landing page, which is a page that describes the dataset. Rather, this URL points directly to the data itself.

id.description: A unique identifier for a thing.

keywords.description: Keywords associated with the data. These may be provided by the data creator or assigned later in a manual or automated manner.

language.description: language in which the information is expressed

last_updated_on.description: Date and Time at which the element was last updated

status.description: Status of the element in terms of its maturity or life cycle

title.description: the official title of the element

was_derived_from.description: A derivation is a transformation of an entity into another, an update of an entity resulting in a new one, or the construction of a new entity based on a pre-existing entity.@en
